cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.MM

The paper deals with the application of deep learning for melanoma detection, which is a computer vision problem, hence cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of generative adversarial networks (GANs) for data augmentation, which falls under the sub-category of generative models (cs.LG). The paper also involves the use of deep learning for classification (cs.AI) and image processing (cs.IR), which are relevant sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with medical imaging, which falls under the sub-category of multimedia (cs.MM).
